# Cursor Rules - Mautic-Nest

Project: Mautic-Nest
Stack: NestJS 11 + Next.js 16 + PostgreSQL + Mastra AI
Vault: ~/tolaria-hermes/projects/mautic-nest/

# Agent Behavior
- Always read PLAN.md for architecture context before making changes
- Follow NestJS module pattern (controller, service, entity per module)
- Use Drizzle ORM for all database queries
- Zod for validation at all boundaries
- Run `npx ultracite check` before commit

# Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode
- NestJS DI patterns (constructor injection)
- PascalCase for classes/decorators, camelCase for methods/variables
- `const` by default, `let` only when needed

# Critical Rules
- NEVER call `workflow.run()` directly on Mastra workflows
- ALWAYS validate input with Zod at API boundaries
- ALWAYS handle errors explicitly with NestJS exception filters
- Events flow: Controller -> Service -> DB. Services never import Controllers

# Commands
dev:      pnpm dev
build:    pnpm build
db:       cd packages/backend && drizzle-kit push
studio:   cd packages/backend && drizzle-kit studio
lint:     npx ultracite check
fix:      npx ultracite fix

# SA Context
- PayFast for payment processing
- POPIA compliance for contact data
- AWS Cape Town for data residency
- ZAR currency for marketplace
